dc_description_s: This data represents zoning for Sauk County, Wisconsin in 2021 and includes the layers 'Sauk_Airport_2021,' 'Sauk_General_2021,' and 'Sauk_Shoreland_2021.' [AIRPORT: The purpose of this data is to regulate the use of property and restrict the height of structures and growth within the designated vicinity of the Tri-County Regional Airport. GENERAL: This feature class is used to maintain and display the current zoning information in the Sauk County GIS. Zoning Districts are administered by Sauk County for all Towns except the Town of Fairfield, Town of Delton, Town of Merrimac, and the Town of Washington. SHORELAND: 'Shoreland‚Äù means lands within the following distances from the ordinary high water mark of navigable waters: 1,000 feet from a lake, pond, or flowage; and 300 feet from a river or stream or to the landward side of the floodplain, whichever distance is greater.]
uw_supplemental_s: This is an archived copy of the data held at UW-Madison. For access to the most current data available, please visit: https://data-saukgis.opendata.arcgis.com/
